        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-12-05 19:33:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nNathaniel, the commit summary line doesn't really explain what this patch does at all. \"LU-2405 tests: Add regression test for LU-2241\" is what people will mostly see about this commit and doesn't really contain much information. \n\nWhen backporting patches, it is better to keep the original commit message as much as possible, so that it is easier to match them together (e.g. if someone else had already cherry-picked some patch back to this branch). In this case it is unlikely, but just a general rule for the future.\n\nSomething like:\n\n LU-2405 tests: verify off-by-one symlink length fix",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
